-- RBC Hires Katz, Carter From Barclays for U.S. Technology
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-03-18T13:30:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-18/rbc-hires-katz-carter-from-barclays-for-u-s-technology.html
RBC Capital Markets, the investment
bank owned by  Royal Bank of Canada (RY) , hired Michal Katz and
Michael Carter from  Barclays (BARC)  Plc as co-heads of the U.S.
technology group in New York.  Katz, 45, was previously head of Barclays’s global software
practice within the global technology investment-banking group,
Toronto-based RBC said today in an e-mailed statement. Carter,
45, led the enterprise and information-services sectors within
the same group. Both bankers had similar roles at Lehman
Brothers Holdings Inc. before Barclays.  RBC also hired Erik-Jaap Molenaar, 41, from Barclays for
mergers and acquisitions in the technology group, according to
the statement. He’ll be based in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Doug Alexander in Toronto at 
 dalexander3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
